theorem
(I is (p-ideal of X) iff (for x holds (for y holds (for z holds (( ( x \ z ) \ ( y \ z ) ) in I implies ( x \ y ) in I)))))
proof
thus (I is (p-ideal of X) implies (for x holds (for y holds (for z holds (( ( x \ z ) \ ( y \ z ) ) in I implies ( x \ y ) in I)))))
proof
assume A1: I is (p-ideal of X);
let x;
let y;
let z;
assume that
A2: ( ( x \ z ) \ ( y \ z ) ) in I;
( ( ( x \ z ) \ ( y \ z ) ) \ ( x \ y ) ) = ( 0. X ) by BCIALG_1:def 3;
then ( ( x \ z ) \ ( y \ z ) ) <= ( x \ y ) by BCIALG_1:def 11;
hence thesis by A1,A2,CKB27:1;
end;

assume A3: (for x holds (for y holds (for z holds (( ( x \ z ) \ ( y \ z ) ) in I implies ( x \ y ) in I))));
A4: (for x holds (for y holds (for z holds ((( ( x \ z ) \ ( y \ z ) ) in I & y in I) implies x in I))))
proof
let x;
let y;
let z;
assume that
A5: ( ( x \ z ) \ ( y \ z ) ) in I
and
A6: y in I;
( x \ y ) in I by A3,A5;
hence thesis by A6,BCIALG_1:def 18;
end;
( 0. X ) in I by BCIALG_1:def 18;
hence thesis by A4,CKB23:def 1;
end;
